### Structure

In 2023, Indonesia's Gross Domestic Product (GDP) at current market prices reached IDR 20,892.4 trillion. The production side saw its highest growth in the Transportation and Storage sector, with an impressive 13.96% increase. Regionally, the provinces of Maluku and Papua, Sulawesi, and Kalimantan experienced the most significant growth, with year-on-year increases of 6.94%, 6.37%, and 5.43%, respectively. Meanwhile, the island of Java, contributing 57.05% to the national economy, recorded a growth of 4.96%.

